Interface Layout<V,E>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.apache.commons.collections15.Transformer<V,Point2D>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    PersistentLayout<V,E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractLayout, AggregateLayout, BalloonLayout, CachingLayout, CircleLayout, DAGLayout, FRLayout, FRLayout2, ISOMLayout, KKLayout, LayoutDecorator, ObservableCachingLayout, PersistentLayoutImpl, RadialTreeLayout, SpringLayout, SpringLayout2, StaticLayout, TreeLayout

    public interface Layout<V,E>
extends org.apache.commons.collections15.Transformer<V,Point2D>
    A generalized interface is a mechanism for returning (x,y) coordinates from vertices. In general, most of these methods are used to both control and get information from the layout algorithm.

    Author:
    danyelf, tom nelson
